      "question": "In a circle with centre $O$ and radius $7$ $cm$, a chord $AB$ subtends an angle of $90^\\circ$ at the centre. If the area of the minor segment formed by chord $AB$ is $A_1$ and the area of the corresponding major sector is $A_2$, then the value of $A_2 - A_1$ in $cm^2$ is:",
      "answer": "(A)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Identify the area of the minor sector $OAB$ as $\\frac{90}{360} \\times \\pi r^2 = \\frac{1}{4} \\times \\pi \\times 7^2 = \\frac{49\\pi}{4}$.",
          "Calculate the area of $\\triangle OAB = \\frac{1}{2} \\times r \\times r \\times \\sin(90^\\circ) = \\frac{1}{2} \\times 49 \\times 1 = 24.5$.",
          "Determine $A_1 = \\text{Area of sector} - \\text{Area of } \\triangle OAB = \\frac{49\\pi}{4} - 24.5$.",
          "Determine $A_2 = \\text{Total Area} - \\text{Area of minor sector} = \\pi r^2 - \\frac{1}{4}\\pi r^2 = \\frac{3}{4}\\pi r^2 = \\frac{3}{4}\\pi(49) = \\frac{147\\pi}{4}$.",
          "Calculate $A_2 - A_1 = \\frac{147\\pi}{4} - (\\frac{49\\pi}{4} - 24.5) = \\frac{98\\pi}{4} + 24.5 = 24.5\\pi + 24.5 = 24.5(\\pi + 1)$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$A_1 = \\frac{90}{360} \\pi (7)^2 - \\frac{1}{2}(7)(7) = \\frac{49\\pi}{4} - 24.5 \\\\ A_2 = \\pi(7)^2 - \\frac{49\\pi}{4} = \\frac{147\\pi}{4} \\\\ A_2 - A_1 = \\frac{147\\pi}{4} - \\frac{49\\pi}{4} + 24.5 \\\\ A_2 - A_1 = \\frac{98\\pi}{4} + 24.5 = 24.5\\pi + 24.5 = 24.5(\\pi + 1)$"
      },
